Jenkins Pipeline Mental Model

Note1:
pipeline
agent
parameters
environment
options
stages
stage
steps
post

Note2:
stage
  → when
  → steps
    → container
      → dir
        → withCredentials
          → script, only for Groovy logic
          → sh


input(...) {
    // Nothing is allowed here
}

timeout(...) {
    // Steps to run within the timeout
}

when - is used at stage level
parallel - is used at stage level
if-else - is used at steps level and inside a script block. It's complete groovy syntax
Jenkins Pipeline steps do not have names.


post {
    failure means the step/build failed
    unstable means the build completed, but there were issues
    success means everything passed
    always runs regardless of result
}



===========================================================================
Terrafrom Backend:

terraform init -backend-config="backend/dev.hcl"

Terrafrom combines the backend block with the file passed through -backend-config

backend.tf:
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    encrypt      = true
    use_lockfile = true
  }
}

backend/dev.hcl:
bucket = "my-terraform-state-bucket"
key    = "eks/dev/terraform.tfstate"
region = "us-east-1"

terraform init -backend-config="backend/dev.hcl"

terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket       = "my-terraform-state-bucket"
    key          = "eks/dev/terraform.tfstate"
    region       = "us-east-1"
    encrypt      = true
    use_lockfile = true
  }
}

Terraform throws an error if dev.hcl contains arguments that the selected backend does not support.